race.description: Computer Talk - Business I.t Experts Handicap
race.comment: SO BRAVE (4) is a lightly raced 5yo who looks well placed getting to 2400m fourth up from a spell. A surprise winner fresh at a mile, he's been good in two runs since, unsuited staying at 2040m last time at Moonee Valley when wanting more ground. This looks a good race for him. MY ROCA FELLA (6) stuck on gamely out to 2200m last time at Sale, no match for the winner but doing well to beat the rest. Two goes at this trip have been just fair but he's going better now and should give a sight. JEALOUS (9) is going okay, good to the line over 2025m last time. Can't see this trip being an issue off that run. FOIRE DE TRONE (12) is always thereabouts and is a must-include.
